chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Heart murmurs and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content:
You don’t need to tell DVLA if you have a heart murmur.

You must stop driving for at least 1 month if you have heart failure. You must only restart driving when your doctor tells you it’s safe.

Read ‘Car or motorcycle drivers with heart conditions’ for more information.

chunks.html_content:
You must tell DVLA if you have a heart murmur.

Fill in form VOCH1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
